<doc id="319751" wikidata="Q667552" url="?curid=319751" title="Maquis shrubland">
<text>&#x27; ( , , ) or &#x27; ( , ; often in Italian; , ; ; ; ) is a savanna-like shrubland biome in the Mediterranean region, typically consisting of densely growing evergreen shrubs.

Maquis is characterized by plants of the family Lamiaceae, genera &quot;Laurus&quot; and &quot;Myrtus&quot;, and species &quot;Olea europaea&quot;, &quot;Ceratonia siliqua&quot;, and &quot;Ficus carica&quot;. It is similar to garrigue.

==See also==
*Mining maquis
* Maquis (disambiguation)
* Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub

